FBIS4-32881 "drlat104_r_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-104 Daily Report 28 May 1994 Peru Congress Approves Fujimori's Trip Abroad Congress Approves Fujimori's Trip Abroad PY3005205694 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0301 GMT 28 May 94 PY3005205694 Madrid EFE Spanish BFN [Text] Lima, 27 May (EFE) -- Congressional sources have reported that the Peruvian Congress today authorized the journey by President Alberto Fujimori to the Fourth Ibero-American Summit in Cartagena de Indias (Colombia), and to Japan and the PRC. In a full session the Democratic Constituent Congress (CCD) today approved President Fujimori's trip abroad: from 14 to 16 June to the Ibero-American summit, and from 2 to 13 June to Japan and the PRC. The visit to Japan will begin on 5 June, while he will be in the PRC from 8 to 12 June. Congressional authorization for the president's trips abroad is a requirement established by the Constitution.
